// EFFECTIVE UNTIL JUNE 30, 2015 PER CHAPTERS 280 AND 281 OF 2011 //
A registration issued under this subtitle expires on December 31 of each odd-numbered year unless the registration is renewed for a 2-year term as provided in subsection (b) of this section.
On or before December 1 of the year of expiration, a registration may be renewed for a 2-year term if the registrant:
Otherwise is entitled to be registered;
Pays to the Commissioner the renewal fee established under § 12-1006 of this subtitle; and
Submits to the Commissioner a renewal application on the form that the Commissioner requires.
